Next, the structural information and chemical composition of teallite crystal are determined using HRTEM and EDXS characterization techniques. FigureÂ 2a shows a HRTEM image of teallite crystal with the determined lattice spacing of 2.02 Ã and 2.14 Ã along the zigzag direction (a-axis) and the armchair direction (b-axis), with the intersection angle of around 90Â°. These spacing are found consistent with the (200) and (020) sets of planes for the orthorhombic teallite crystal. Both (110) and (1Â¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
